Just like on so many other issues in politics and society, <br>
we remain polarized on this issue and just talk past each <br>
other.  Nice try, PBS.  You got yourselves some publicity,<br>
but I don't think this will accomplish anything.<br><br>
I had intended to add more thoughts along the lines of my<br>
earlier posting, but I recognize the futility.  It's the<br>
same here as it is on on any discussion or newsgroup that<br>
I have ever explored on the Internet.<br><br>
Somehow, I think we're beyond reconciliation and agreement<br>
on a middle ground on practically every issue, not just on<br>
Vietnam.  Would even an impending collision with an asteroid<br>
bring everyone together?  I think not.<br><br>
A more likely scenario is the continued Balkanization of<br>
America, perhaps ending with calls for legal, peaceful<br>
secession of certain states and regions.<br><br>
I'm not sure that would be so bad.  Then there would be NO<br>
superpowers left in the world.<br><br>
Remember, you heard it here first!<br>

